WEBVTT

01:16.201 --> 01:19.745
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

01:21.706 --> 01:22.873
Albert: WHOOPEE!

01:23.041 --> 01:25.000
Laura, Albert, Andy:
NO MORE PENCILS, NO MORE BOOKS!

01:25.168 --> 01:27.711
NO MORE TEACHER'S
DIRTY LOOKS!

01:27.879 --> 01:29.546
NO SCHOOL
TILL NEXT FALL!

01:29.714 --> 01:30.714
YAY!

01:30.882 --> 01:31.882
FREE AS
BIRDS!

01:32.050 --> 01:34.051
OH, WE GOT THE
WHOLE SUMMER!

01:34.219 --> 01:35.302
- NO HOMEWORK!
- NO TESTS!

01:35.470 --> 01:36.762
WE GOT TO SEE
KEZIA, COME ON!

01:36.930 --> 01:38.555
YEAH!

01:38.723 --> 01:40.641
Albert: WHOOPEE!

01:46.231 --> 01:47.773
THAT SHOULD DO IT.

01:47.941 --> 01:50.484
YES.

01:50.652 --> 01:53.529
NOW, LET'S SEE
WHO'S WRITTEN WHAT

01:53.696 --> 01:56.698
TO OLD PRUNE-FACE
HARRIET OLESON.

01:56.866 --> 01:58.158
AH.

01:58.326 --> 01:59.660
NOW...

01:59.828 --> 02:01.078
OH.

02:01.246 --> 02:02.913
AIN'T THAT A SHAME?

02:03.081 --> 02:07.709
THEY'RE ALL OUT OF
THE FRENCH CORTEL
CORSETS SHE ORDERED.

02:07.877 --> 02:11.130
THE VENUS MODEL,
NO LESS.

02:11.297 --> 02:13.632
"COMFORT AND ELEGANCE
COMBINED--

02:13.800 --> 02:15.217
"A SUMMER CORSET--

02:15.385 --> 02:17.511
"SATEEN STRIPED,

02:17.679 --> 02:21.098
REINFORCED FRONT STEELS
AND TWO SIDE STEELS."

02:21.266 --> 02:25.060
SHE'D DO JUST AS WELL WITH
A ROLL OF BALING WIRE.

02:25.228 --> 02:26.436
Laura: HI, KEZIA!
CAN WE COME IN?

02:26.604 --> 02:29.314
OH! COME ON IN!

02:29.482 --> 02:30.524
[LAUGHS]

02:30.692 --> 02:31.942
HELLO.

02:32.110 --> 02:33.944
Laura: THERE'S
NO MORE SCHOOL TILL
THE FALL, KEZIA.

02:34.112 --> 02:35.988
WE CAN COME TO
YOUR PLACE MOST
EVERY DAY NOW.

02:36.156 --> 02:38.490
AFTER WE DO OUR
CHORES, OF COURSE,
IF YOU'D LIKE.

02:38.658 --> 02:39.700
LIKE?

02:39.868 --> 02:41.994
I'D LOVE IT!

02:42.162 --> 02:44.121
YOU KNOW
THE WELCOME
MAT'S ALWAYS OUT

02:44.289 --> 02:46.623
FOR YOU DARLINGS
AT LAKE KEZIA.

02:46.791 --> 02:49.501
OH, WE'LL HAVE
A MARVELOUS SUMMER.

02:49.669 --> 02:51.753
Kezia: WE WILL,
THE 4 OF US.

02:51.921 --> 02:53.797
HOW LONG ARE YOU GOING
TO BE FILLING IN HERE

02:53.965 --> 02:55.007
FOR MS. FOSTER?

02:55.175 --> 02:57.134
OH, SHE COMES
BACK TOMORROW.

02:57.302 --> 02:59.469
Andy: THEN WE CAN
START FISHING AND
FROGGING TOMORROW.

02:59.637 --> 03:01.054
YEAH, AND SINGING
SEA CHANTIES,

03:01.222 --> 03:03.891
AND LISTENING TO ALL
THE STORIES ABOUT
ALL YOUR HUSBANDS.

03:04.058 --> 03:07.352
OH, YES, EACH OF
THEM ARE RARE MEN.

03:07.520 --> 03:12.065
WHISKEY JAKE CURRY,
SMILING WILLY HORNE,

03:12.233 --> 03:17.404
HARPOON HARRY WALSH,
AND HANDSOME TOMMY BANE.

03:17.572 --> 03:19.656
OH, DON'T FORGET
DANCING DANNY RYAN.

03:19.824 --> 03:22.743
[LAUGHING]

03:22.911 --> 03:28.457
ALL OF THEM
GOOD SAILORS.

03:28.625 --> 03:30.292
ALL OF THEM GONE.

03:30.460 --> 03:35.881
GONE TO THE SEA,
NEVER TO COME BACK,
BUT NOT FORGOTTEN.

03:36.049 --> 03:38.008
NEVER FORGOTTEN.

03:38.176 --> 03:40.302
WELL, WE KNOW
YOU'VE GOT TO
GET BACK TO WORK.

03:40.470 --> 03:41.678
WE'LL SEE
YOU TOMORROW.

03:41.846 --> 03:46.350
- SEE YOU TOMORROW, KEZIA!
- YEAH, SEE YOU TOMORROW!

03:46.517 --> 03:48.393
OHH...BACK TO WORK.

03:48.561 --> 03:52.022
POLLY, FETCH ME
ANOTHER LETTER.

03:52.190 --> 03:53.690
[CROWING]

03:58.529 --> 04:01.406
THIS SHOULD BE
A TORRID ONE, POLLY.

04:01.574 --> 04:05.619
IT'S FROM NANCY
[INDISTINCT].

04:05.787 --> 04:07.371
WHAT ARE YOU GOING
TO DO THIS SUMMER,
CHILDREN?

04:07.538 --> 04:09.248
I'M JUST GOING
TO REST UP.

04:09.415 --> 04:12.584
I THOUGHT YOU WERE DOING
THAT DURING THE SCHOOL YEAR.
WHAT ABOUT YOU, NELLIE?

04:12.752 --> 04:15.337
OH, I HAVE NO
PLANS, FATHER.

04:15.505 --> 04:17.256
I DO.
[LAUGHS]

04:17.423 --> 04:20.342
IT'S A SURPRISE
FOR ALL OF YOU.

04:20.510 --> 04:23.136
WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE A
SUMMER PLACE.

04:23.304 --> 04:25.722
A SUMMER PLACE? WHY?

04:25.890 --> 04:29.434
WELL, ALL WEALTHY PEOPLE
HAVE SUMMER PLACES...

04:29.602 --> 04:32.020
TO GET AWAY FROM THE HEAT
AND THE BUSTLE OF THE CITY.

04:32.188 --> 04:36.191
WELL, I'LL GRANT YOU
THE HEAT, BUT WHAT
CITY? WHAT BUSTLE?

04:36.359 --> 04:38.527
WE'VE ONLY HAD 3 PEOPLE
IN HERE ALL AFTERNOON!

04:38.695 --> 04:44.241
AH. ALL THE MORE REASON
FOR THE CHILDREN AND ME
TO ENJOY OUR ADVANTAGES.

04:44.409 --> 04:47.577
YOU CAN EASILY
HANDLE THE STORE.

04:47.745 --> 04:49.913
[SARCASTICALLY]
THANKS.

04:50.081 --> 04:52.666
WELL, JUST WHERE
IS THIS PLACE THAT
YOU'RE CONSIDERING?

04:52.834 --> 04:54.084
[LAUGHS]

04:54.252 --> 04:56.295
I'M NOT CONSIDERING, NELS.

04:56.462 --> 04:58.588
I'VE ALREADY SET
THE WHEELS IN MOTION.

04:58.756 --> 05:02.009
IN FACT, I'VE
ALREADY ORDERED
THE SUMMER FURNITURE.

05:02.176 --> 05:05.095
[SARCASTICALLY]
HOW NICE OF YOU
TO CONSULT ME.

05:05.263 --> 05:08.307
BUT JUST WHERE
IS THIS HOUSE?

05:08.474 --> 05:09.766
I TOLD YOU.

05:09.934 --> 05:11.852
IT'S A SURPRISE!

05:12.020 --> 05:13.645
[LAUGHS]

05:15.857 --> 05:18.275
[DUCKS QUACKING]

05:33.333 --> 05:35.208
HEY!
I GOT ONE!

05:35.376 --> 05:36.626
I GOT ONE!

05:36.794 --> 05:38.587
AH! THERE
SHE BLOWS!

05:38.755 --> 05:39.921
LOOK
AT THAT!

05:40.089 --> 05:41.006
OH!

05:41.174 --> 05:43.800
- OH, BOY!
- WHOPPING BIG FISH!

05:43.968 --> 05:45.427
LOOK AT THE SIZE
OF IT!

05:45.595 --> 05:48.680
Kezia: HA HA! I RECKON
THERE'S ENOUGH FISH THERE

05:48.848 --> 05:51.641
FOR A STOMACH-FILLING
SUPPER. HA HA!

05:51.809 --> 05:55.145
LET'S HEAD FOR THE SHORE
AND THE FRYING PAN.

05:55.313 --> 05:58.273
Polly: TIME TO EAT.
TIME TO EAT. LET'S EAT.

05:58.441 --> 06:00.525
[SIZZLING]

06:10.787 --> 06:15.332
OH! I'M SO FULL,
I THINK I'M
GOING TO BUST.

06:15.500 --> 06:16.750
ME TOO.

06:16.918 --> 06:19.169
OH, I ATE
LIKE A HORSE.

06:19.337 --> 06:21.505
THERE'S NOTHING
BETTER FOR A MAN

06:21.672 --> 06:23.715
THAN TO CATCH
HIS OWN SUPPER.

06:23.883 --> 06:26.176
BOY, THAT
SURE IS TRUE.

06:26.344 --> 06:28.637
I USUALLY DON'T
LIKE FISH AT HOME,

06:28.805 --> 06:32.057
BUT WHEN I CATCH IT
MYSELF, IT'S DELICIOUS.

06:32.225 --> 06:34.101
I KNOW WHAT
YOU MEAN.

06:34.268 --> 06:35.519
[LAUGHS]

06:35.686 --> 06:37.312
TELL US A STORY, KEZIA.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.524
- YEAH. TELL US.
- ALL RIGHT, ME PRETTIES.

06:40.691 --> 06:46.196
NOW, DID I EVER
TELL YOU ABOUT HOW
HARPOON HARRY WALSH--

06:46.364 --> 06:49.116
HE WAS ME THIRD
HUSBAND, YOU KNOW--

06:49.283 --> 06:55.497
HOW HE RODE
ON THE BACK OF THE
LOCH NESS MONSTER?

06:55.665 --> 06:56.706
THE WHAT?

06:56.874 --> 06:58.917
Kezia: THE LOCH
NESS MONSTER.

06:59.085 --> 07:03.630
A CREATURE
SO FRIGHTENING THAT
HE BECAME A LEGEND.

07:03.798 --> 07:05.715
IT'S TRUE. I HEARD
ABOUT IT AT SCHOOL.

07:05.883 --> 07:07.426
TELL US
ABOUT IT.

07:07.593 --> 07:10.554
WELL, YOU SEE
THAT HARPOON THERE?

07:10.721 --> 07:15.725
THAT'S THE VERY
SAME HARPOON HE PUT
INTO THE GREAT BEAST.

07:15.893 --> 07:18.770
HE GIVE IT ME AS
A WEDDING PRESENT.

07:18.938 --> 07:20.230
YES, HE SAID HE'D...

07:20.398 --> 07:22.649
HE'D HOOKED ME
GOOD AND PROPER,

07:22.817 --> 07:25.068
AND HE WANTED ME
TO HAVE THE HARPOON

07:25.236 --> 07:27.487
SO THAT I'D
NEVER FORGET.

07:27.655 --> 07:28.738
WELL, DID HE
KILL THE MONSTER?

07:28.906 --> 07:30.907
Kezia: NOW, DON'T
INTERRUPT, NOW.

07:31.075 --> 07:32.033
SORRY.

07:32.201 --> 07:37.414
IT WAS, UH...YES,
IT WAS NOVEMBER...

07:37.582 --> 07:40.709
1832...

07:40.877 --> 07:43.837
ON A LOVELY MORNING.

07:44.005 --> 07:47.507
HARRY WALSH
WAS ON THE LAKE,

07:47.675 --> 07:53.013
AND, UH...HE SPIES
A TREMENDOUS HEAD

07:53.181 --> 07:56.475
COMING RIGHT OUT
OF THE WATER,

07:56.642 --> 07:58.810
NEARLY TOUCHING
THE SKY!

07:58.978 --> 08:02.063
"HA! THERE SHE
BLOWS!" HE SAID.

08:02.231 --> 08:04.107
"THERE SHE BLOWS!"
HA HA!

08:04.275 --> 08:06.151
[WAGON APPROACHING]

08:06.319 --> 08:07.569
OH.

08:07.737 --> 08:09.488
THERE'S SOMEONE
COMING.

08:17.205 --> 08:20.165
IT'S HIM AGAIN!

08:20.333 --> 08:21.416
OH.

08:21.584 --> 08:23.502
I'LL BE BACK.

08:23.669 --> 08:25.962
THAT'S FAR ENOUGH!

08:26.130 --> 08:29.883
THAT'S FAR ENOUGH,
I SAID!

08:30.051 --> 08:32.469
Kezia: YOU'RE
WASTING YOUR
TIME, MR. FLINT.

08:32.637 --> 08:34.971
I'M NOT PAYING
TAXES ON THIS LAND.

08:35.139 --> 08:37.224
I TOLD YOU THAT
THE YEAR BEFORE LAST

08:37.391 --> 08:39.643
AND THE YEAR BEFORE
THAT AND THE YEAR
BEFORE THAT!

08:39.810 --> 08:41.811
I'M NOT HERE TO
COLLECT THE TAXES.

08:41.979 --> 08:44.064
OH, WELL, I'M HAPPY
TO HEAR THAT.

08:44.232 --> 08:46.107
THEY'VE ALREADY
BEEN PAID.

08:46.275 --> 08:48.610
PAID?

08:48.778 --> 08:51.655
WHO PAID THEM?

08:51.822 --> 08:53.532
THE NEW OWNER.

08:53.699 --> 08:54.908
Mr. Flint:
I WARNED YOU.

08:55.076 --> 08:58.495
YOU HAD TO
PAY YOUR TAXES,
BUT YOU WOULDN'T.

08:58.663 --> 09:02.123
IT'S BEEN
AUCTIONED OFF.

09:02.291 --> 09:03.291
WHAT?

09:03.459 --> 09:05.794
WELL, I SENT YOU
A LETTER ABOUT IT.

09:05.962 --> 09:08.838
I NEVER READ
ME OWN MAIL.

09:09.006 --> 09:10.757
Mr. Flint:
YOU SHOULD
HAVE READ IT.

09:10.925 --> 09:12.092
[SIGHS]

09:12.260 --> 09:14.511
LOOK, I'M SORRY.
THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO.

09:14.679 --> 09:19.015
THE NEW OWNER IS GOING
TO TAKE POSSESSION
OF THE PROPERTY TOMORROW.

09:25.273 --> 09:26.982
I'M SORRY.

09:56.554 --> 09:59.472
ALWAYS A CASTLE,

09:59.640 --> 10:03.685
AND NOW THEY'RE
GOING TO CAST ME
OFF THE PLACE.

10:03.853 --> 10:07.063
I WANTED TO SPEND
ME LAST DAYS.

10:07.231 --> 10:10.066
THEY CAN'T DO THIS
TO YOU, KEZIA.

10:10.234 --> 10:11.818
WE WON'T LET THEM.

10:11.986 --> 10:16.448
WELL, THERE'S NOTHING
WE CAN DO ABOUT IT, LADS.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.908
WHY DIDN'T YOU PAY
YOUR TAXES, KEZIA?

10:19.076 --> 10:21.369
WELL, I DIDN'T
HAVE THE MONEY.

10:21.537 --> 10:24.497
I MEAN, TAXES
IS LIKE JOBS--

10:24.665 --> 10:27.459
THEY'RE FOR THE YOUNG.

10:30.004 --> 10:33.340
WHO WOULD BE MEAN
ENOUGH TO GO AND BUY
YOUR OWN PROPERTY

10:33.507 --> 10:36.760
RIGHT OUT
FROM UNDERNEATH
YOU LIKE THIS?

10:36.927 --> 10:39.512
I DON'T KNOW, LAD.

10:39.680 --> 10:41.806
I DON'T KNOW.

10:41.974 --> 10:43.350
AHH.

10:43.517 --> 10:45.226
BUT I TELL YOU,

10:45.394 --> 10:49.105
I'M NOT
GOING TO GIVE UP
WITHOUT A FIGHT.

10:49.273 --> 10:50.482
HARRIET, YOU
CAN'T DO THIS!

10:50.650 --> 10:51.983
OH, FOR
HEAVEN'S SAKES!

10:52.151 --> 10:54.194
IT IS OVER.
I'VE DONE IT, AND
THAT'S ENOUGH.

10:54.362 --> 10:56.738
BUT TO EVICT
AN OLD WOMAN?
SHE'LL BE HOMELESS!

10:56.906 --> 11:00.617
OH, NELS!
WHAT I DID WAS
PERFECTLY LEGAL.

11:00.785 --> 11:02.327
I AM NOT TALKING
ABOUT THE LAW.

11:02.495 --> 11:04.204
I AM TALKING ABOUT
A HUMAN BEING!

11:04.372 --> 11:06.956
WELL! I'M A HUMAN
BEING, TOO!

11:07.124 --> 11:10.543
AND I WANTED
THAT LAKE!

11:10.711 --> 11:13.463
NOW, HERE, HELP ME
WITH THIS THING.

11:13.631 --> 11:15.590
IT'S NOT WHAT
I WANTED, BUT IT
WILL HAVE TO DO.

11:15.758 --> 11:17.300
HARRIET, PLEASE,
IF YOU'LL JUST--

11:17.468 --> 11:19.260
OH, JUST
CINCH ME UP.

11:20.596 --> 11:21.596
[GRUNTS]

11:21.764 --> 11:22.972
THE PROBLEM WITH YOU

11:23.140 --> 11:26.559
IS YOU DON'T
HAVE A SENSE OF
BUSINESS AT ALL.

11:26.727 --> 11:30.980
I MEAN, IT WAS $50.
IT WAS A STEAL!

11:31.148 --> 11:32.190
I MEAN--OH!

11:32.358 --> 11:35.860
IT'S TOO TIGHT,
FOR HEAVEN'S SAKE.

11:36.028 --> 11:37.737
[SIGHS]

11:37.905 --> 11:40.240
THERE.
THAT'S BETTER.

11:40.408 --> 11:41.324
OH, NELS.

11:41.492 --> 11:44.369
OH, I'LL MAKE IT
A SOCIAL CENTER.

11:44.537 --> 11:46.329
I'LL BRING
CULTURE AND GRACE

11:46.497 --> 11:50.291
TO THE PLEBEIAN
POPULACE OF
WALNUT GROVE.

11:50.459 --> 11:51.710
WELL, YOU WON'T
BRING IT TO ME.

11:51.877 --> 11:52.836
STEALING THAT
OLD WOMAN'S HOME!

11:53.003 --> 11:54.379
OH!

11:54.547 --> 11:57.006
YOU CAN GO OUT THERE
AND SPEND THE SUMMER.
I'M STAYING IN TOWN.

11:57.174 --> 12:01.010
WELL, YOU'LL BE SORRY,
NELS OLESON. YOU JUST
STAY RIGHT HERE IN TOWN.

12:01.178 --> 12:04.556
YOU'LL BE MISERABLE ALL
SUMMER LONG...ALONE.

12:04.724 --> 12:08.184
YES, ALONE.
THE WAY I LIKE IT.

12:08.352 --> 12:11.521
OH, YOU--
OH! NELS!

12:11.689 --> 12:14.190
I SEE YOU'RE
FINALLY FIT TO
BE TIED, HARRIET.

12:14.358 --> 12:16.693
NELS!

12:16.861 --> 12:19.362
OH, FOR HEAVEN'S SAKES!

12:19.530 --> 12:21.448
[HAMMERING]

12:28.205 --> 12:30.457
WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF IT, ALICE?

12:30.624 --> 12:32.917
YOU KNOW
WHAT I THINK.

12:33.085 --> 12:35.920
COME ON.
I'M REALLY PROUD
OF THAT MOOSE HEAD.

12:36.088 --> 12:38.715
I'M SURE THE
MOOSE WAS, TOO.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.967
I DIDN'T HEAR NO
COMPLAINTS WHEN
WE HAD THE MEAT.

12:41.135 --> 12:44.429
THE ANIMAL WASN'T
STARING AT ME
WHILE WE ATE.

12:44.597 --> 12:47.098
COME ON. THOSE EYES
ARE MADE OUT OF GLASS.

12:47.266 --> 12:48.725
YOU LIKE IT,
DON'T YOU, SON?

12:48.893 --> 12:50.226
I SUPPOSE.

12:50.394 --> 12:53.313
I THOUGHT I'D
GET SOME SUPPORT
OUT OF YOU, ANYWAY.

12:53.481 --> 12:55.064
WELL, I'M SORRY.
I JUST...

12:55.232 --> 12:57.734
CAN'T STOP WORRYING
ABOUT KEZIA.

12:57.902 --> 13:00.695
HOW COME THEY MAKE
OLD PEOPLE PAY
TAXES, ANYWAY?

13:00.863 --> 13:03.573
I--I DON'T KNOW, SON.

13:03.741 --> 13:04.741
IT AIN'T RIGHT.

13:04.909 --> 13:07.494
MAYBE THEY'LL
CHANGE IT SOMETIME.

13:07.661 --> 13:09.412
THAT WON'T HELP KEZIA.

13:09.580 --> 13:12.415
Jonathan: YEAH, I'LL TELL
YOU WHAT, SON. WHY DON'T
YOU AND I GO FROGGING?

13:12.583 --> 13:13.750
THAT WILL TAKE YOUR
MIND OFF OF IT.

13:13.918 --> 13:15.835
- OKAY. BYE, MA!
- WE WON'T BE LONG, ALICE.

13:16.003 --> 13:17.921
Alice:
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT ME.

13:18.088 --> 13:20.924
I'LL JUST SIT HERE AND
TALK TO YOUR FRIEND.

13:44.156 --> 13:46.407
ARE YOU SURE YOU
WOULDN'T LIKE SOME
MORE PIE, REVEREND?

13:46.575 --> 13:50.411
WHAT I'D LIKE AND WHAT
I SHOULD HAVE, CAROLINE,
ARE TWO DIFFERENT THINGS.

13:50.579 --> 13:51.538
THANK YOU,
BUT NO.

13:51.705 --> 13:53.122
I FIGURED IT WOULD
BE MRS. OLESON

13:53.290 --> 13:55.834
THAT WOULD TAKE POOR
OLD KEZIA'S PROPERTY
AWAY FROM HER.

13:56.001 --> 13:57.544
YEAH, SHE COULD HARDLY
WAIT TO TELL ME.

13:57.711 --> 14:01.214
SHE WANTS ME TO COME TO TEA
AS SOON AS SHE GETS SETTLED.

14:01.382 --> 14:02.590
I HOPE YOU SAID NO.

14:02.758 --> 14:03.716
Caroline:
LAURA.

14:03.884 --> 14:05.301
Alden: THAT'S ALL
RIGHT, CAROLINE.

14:05.469 --> 14:07.554
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I TOLD HER I HAD
A VERY FULL SCHEDULE,

14:07.721 --> 14:11.140
BUT I AM GOING OUT THERE
TOMORROW WHEN MRS. OLESON
TAKES POSSESSION.

14:11.308 --> 14:13.643
I'M JUST A LITTLE BIT
AFRAID OF KEZIA'S TEMPER.

14:13.811 --> 14:16.521
BOY, SHE WAS
HOPPING MAD TODAY.

14:16.689 --> 14:18.356
WELL, I THOUGHT MY PRESENCE
THERE MIGHT MAKE THINGS

14:18.524 --> 14:21.776
A LITTLE MORE...
CHRISTIAN, SHALL WE SAY?

14:21.944 --> 14:23.653
CAN WE GO WITH YOU?

14:23.821 --> 14:26.155
WELL, I'M SURE THAT
REVEREND ALDEN CAN
HANDLE IT, HALF-PINT.

14:26.323 --> 14:28.658
Alden: WELL, I KNOW
I CAN HANDLE IT, CHARLES,

14:28.826 --> 14:31.160
BUT YOU KNOW HOW KEZIA
FEELS ABOUT THE YOUNG ONES.

14:31.328 --> 14:33.955
IT MIGHT BE GOOD FOR HER
TO HAVE THEM OUT THERE.

14:34.123 --> 14:36.875
WHATEVER YOU
SAY, REVEREND.

14:37.042 --> 14:39.127
I WILL PICK YOU
TWO UP AT 7:00.

14:44.383 --> 14:46.509
[DUCKS QUACKING]

14:49.346 --> 14:53.349
I WON'T. I WON'T
LEAVE THE SHIP
WITHOUT A FIGHT!

14:53.517 --> 14:56.603
NOW, KEZIA,
VIOLENCE NEVER DID
ACCOMPLISH ANYTHING.

14:56.770 --> 14:58.271
BEGGING YOUR
PARDON, REVEREND,

14:58.439 --> 14:59.689
YOU'RE WRONG THERE.

14:59.857 --> 15:02.692
IT WOULD GIVE ME
A HEAP OF SATISFACTION

15:02.860 --> 15:05.820
TO RUN THIS THROUGH
THAT OLD SEA COW

15:05.988 --> 15:07.906
LIKE A PIG ON A SPIT!

15:08.073 --> 15:11.034
I AM POSITIVE YOU
DON'T MEAN THAT, KEZIA.

15:11.201 --> 15:15.371
POSITIVE MEANS WRONG
FROM THE TOP OF YOUR VOICE!

15:15.539 --> 15:17.582
HERE SHE COMES NOW.

15:21.712 --> 15:22.879
HERE SHE COMES.

15:23.047 --> 15:25.757
SHE'S COMING TO
TAKE MY PROPERTY!

15:25.925 --> 15:27.800
[DUCKS QUACKING]

15:39.229 --> 15:41.731
ALL RIGHT,
CHILDREN...
COME ALONG.

15:41.899 --> 15:44.150
I AIN'T GETTING OUT
AS LONG AS SHE'S
GOT THAT HARPOON.

15:47.571 --> 15:49.364
NOW, KEZIA...

15:49.531 --> 15:51.908
I'VE COME TO
TAKE POSSESSION
OF MY PROPERTY.

15:52.076 --> 15:55.411
POSSESSION
IS 9 POINTS OF
THE LAW, THEY SAY,

15:55.579 --> 15:58.581
AND I AM THE
ONE POSSESSING
THIS PROPERTY

15:58.749 --> 16:00.583
AND THIS HARPOON.

16:00.751 --> 16:03.086
YOU KEEP THAT OLD
CROW AWAY FROM ME.

16:03.253 --> 16:05.755
WHO ARE YOU CALLING
AN OLD CROW?

16:05.923 --> 16:07.465
YOU...YOU BEACHED
WHALE, YOU!

16:07.633 --> 16:10.593
OH, YOU LITTLE
SILLY TOAD! GET
OFF MY PROPERTY!

16:10.761 --> 16:12.178
- A TOAD?
- YES!

16:12.346 --> 16:13.596
THIS IS MY
PROPERTY!

16:13.764 --> 16:15.431
DON'T WORRY.
I'LL HANDLE IT.

16:15.599 --> 16:17.016
Kezia: YOU GET
OFF MY PROPERTY!

16:17.184 --> 16:19.102
Alden: LADIES, THIS IS
NO WAY TO BE ACTING,

16:19.269 --> 16:21.688
EITHER ONE OF YOU.
THIS IS NOT CHRISTIAN.

16:21.855 --> 16:23.439
I'LL TELL
YOU WHAT'S
CHRISTIAN!

16:23.607 --> 16:24.899
Alden: WAIT!
STOP THIS!

16:25.067 --> 16:26.818
Harriet: GET AWAY!
GET OFF! GET OFF!

16:26.986 --> 16:28.069
Alden: LADIES!

16:28.237 --> 16:29.779
Harriet: SHE'S
AN ANIMAL! OH!

16:29.947 --> 16:31.614
GET HER AWAY
FROM ME! OH!

16:31.782 --> 16:36.285
LOOKS LIKE THE REVEREND
WAS WRONG ABOUT BEING
ABLE TO HANDLE IT.

16:36.453 --> 16:37.662
[HARRIET SCREAMING]
[POLLY CAWING]

16:37.830 --> 16:38.997
Harriet: OH!

16:39.164 --> 16:40.456
Alden: STOP IT!

16:40.624 --> 16:42.000
Kezia:
YOU ANIMAL!

16:42.167 --> 16:43.543
OH! LET ME UP!

16:43.711 --> 16:46.629
YEAH! OH, BOY!

16:46.797 --> 16:49.132
Polly: FIGHT.
FIGHT. FIGHT.

16:49.299 --> 16:50.299
OH!

16:50.467 --> 16:52.135
STOP IT!
STOP IT!

16:52.302 --> 16:56.472
NOW, STOP IT BEFORE I
FORGET I'M A MINISTER
AND LOSE MY TEMPER!

16:56.640 --> 16:59.058
REVEREND
ALDEN, PLEASE.

16:59.226 --> 17:00.852
NOW, THAT'S BETTER.

17:01.020 --> 17:02.103
[GROANS]

17:02.271 --> 17:05.064
NOW, WE ARE TALKING
ABOUT KEZIA'S HOME.

17:05.232 --> 17:09.694
SURELY WE CAN WORK OUT
SOME KIND OF REASONABLE
AND CHARITABLE COMPROMISE.

17:09.862 --> 17:13.156
WHY, LIKE WHAT?

17:13.323 --> 17:16.242
LIKE SOME WAY
THAT KEZIA COULD
STAY ON HERE.

17:16.410 --> 17:17.577
WELL...

17:17.745 --> 17:19.662
UH, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT.

17:19.830 --> 17:23.082
Alden: IT IS
THE CHRISTIAN THING
TO DO, MRS. OLESON.

17:23.250 --> 17:26.711
Nellie: MOTHER,
SOMEONE'S GOT TO DO
THE COOKING AND CLEANING.

17:26.879 --> 17:28.963
Willie: AND ALL
THE CHORES, TOO.

17:30.340 --> 17:33.593
THAT'S VERY TRUE,
CHILDREN, AND AS
THE REVEREND SAYS,

17:33.761 --> 17:36.846
IT IS THE CHRISTIAN
THING TO DO.

17:37.014 --> 17:38.848
VERY WELL.

17:39.016 --> 17:40.183
SHE CAN STAY,

17:40.350 --> 17:44.187
BUT I'M AFRAID THERE'S
NOWHERE FOR HER TO SLEEP

17:44.354 --> 17:47.273
EXCEPT IN THE SHED.

17:49.401 --> 17:50.985
KEZIA?

17:53.697 --> 17:57.283
RECKON I'VE GOT
NO CHOICE, REVEREND.

17:57.451 --> 18:00.203
I LOVE THIS PLACE.

18:00.370 --> 18:03.831
I'VE BEEN MOVING
ON FOR 80 YEARS.

18:03.999 --> 18:07.418
NOW I'VE GOT
NOWHERE TO GO...

18:07.586 --> 18:10.588
EXCEPT ME GRAVE.

18:14.384 --> 18:16.886
Alden: ALL RIGHT,
IT'S SETTLED.

18:17.054 --> 18:18.721
YES.

18:31.902 --> 18:33.820
WE'RE SORRY, KEZIA.

18:33.987 --> 18:38.407
WELL, ANYWAY, I'VE GOT
A ROOF OVER ME HEAD.

18:40.577 --> 18:42.411
SOME ROOF--

18:42.579 --> 18:45.414
ON A TOOL SHED.

18:45.582 --> 18:48.417
WELL, BEGGARS
CAN'T BE CHOOSERS.

18:48.585 --> 18:49.752
[SNIFFLES]

18:49.920 --> 18:54.799
YOU WILL COME AND SEE
ME SOMETIME, WON'T YOU?

18:54.967 --> 18:56.509
WE WILL.

19:02.516 --> 19:04.350
POLLY! COME ON.

19:04.518 --> 19:05.935
[POLLY CAWING]

19:17.906 --> 19:19.073
ALL RIGHT,
CHILDREN...

19:19.241 --> 19:21.325
COME ALONG,
LET'S GET
THE BAGS OUT.

19:54.067 --> 19:57.111
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

19:57.279 --> 19:58.946
ALL RIGHT, NOW,
MURIEL, WATCH ME,

19:59.114 --> 20:01.699
BECAUSE THIS CAN'T BE
ALL THAT DIFFICULT,
I'M SURE.

20:01.867 --> 20:05.578
NOW, YELLOW
BULL'S-EYE--

20:05.746 --> 20:06.829
OH!

20:06.997 --> 20:08.497
GOOD HEAVENS!

20:08.665 --> 20:12.168
WELL, ONLY AN INDIAN
CAN SHOOT THESE
THINGS, ANYWAY.

20:12.336 --> 20:15.171
- HONESTLY.
- HARRIET, MIGHT I TRY THAT?

20:15.339 --> 20:17.173
- OH. YEAH.
- THANK YOU.

20:17.341 --> 20:18.716
OF COURSE.

20:34.399 --> 20:35.608
KEZIA!

20:35.776 --> 20:38.277
BRING REFRESHMENTS
FOR MY GUESTS!

20:40.322 --> 20:41.864
I THOUGHT IT
WAS RATHER FUN.

20:42.032 --> 20:43.366
Harriet: KEZIA!

20:43.533 --> 20:44.867
Kezia: OH.

20:45.035 --> 20:46.077
Harriet:
KEZIA!

20:46.245 --> 20:49.622
"KEZIA! KEZIA!"
DAY AND NIGHT.

20:49.790 --> 20:52.041
I'M GETTING SICK OF
HEARING ME OWN NAME.

20:52.209 --> 20:54.043
WHAT HAS BEEN
KEEPING YOU?

20:54.211 --> 20:56.170
YOU ARE AS SLOW
AS MOLASSES!

20:56.338 --> 20:57.380
OH, FOR
HEAVEN'S SAKES,

20:57.547 --> 20:59.048
WILL YOU PLEASE
SERVE THE GUESTS

20:59.216 --> 21:00.258
AND MAKE SOME
MORE LEMONADE?

21:00.425 --> 21:01.717
AND START SUPPER
RIGHT AWAY,

21:01.885 --> 21:04.262
BECAUSE WE'RE
GOING TO HAVE
12 GUESTS.

21:04.429 --> 21:06.264
YES, MA'AM.

21:06.431 --> 21:07.723
AND HURRY UP!

21:07.891 --> 21:10.393
WHY, FOR
HEAVEN'S SAKES!

21:14.231 --> 21:19.235
SHE'S GOING TO KILL
POOR OLD KEZIA MAKING
HER WORK LIKE THAT.

21:19.403 --> 21:21.779
JUST WISH
WE COULD DO
SOMETHING FOR HER.

21:21.947 --> 21:23.739
YEAH, BUT WHAT?

21:27.536 --> 21:29.537
I DON'T KNOW.

21:47.097 --> 21:50.391
Caroline:
"THEN BRER RABBIT,
HE SQUALLS OUT,

21:50.559 --> 21:53.269
"DIS DE WAY
A BIG MAN SPIT!

21:53.437 --> 21:57.523
"AND WITH THAT, HE
TILTS OVER THE BIG
TUB OF SLOP WATER,

21:57.691 --> 21:59.900
"AND WHEN THE OTHER
CREATURES HEARD IT COME

22:00.068 --> 22:01.861
"A-SLOSHIN' DOWN
THE STAIR STEPS,

22:02.029 --> 22:04.697
"BY JINGO, THEY ALL
HEISTED THEMSELVES

22:04.865 --> 22:07.074
"OUT OF THAT HOUSE
LICKETY-SPLIT.

22:07.242 --> 22:09.160
"SOME WENT SAILING
OUT THE BACK DOOR,

22:09.328 --> 22:10.411
"SOME OUT
THE FRONT DOOR.

22:10.579 --> 22:12.496
SOME FELL
OUT THE WINDOW."

22:12.664 --> 22:14.457
[LAUGHTER]

22:14.624 --> 22:16.667
"THEN BRER RABBIT,

22:16.835 --> 22:19.045
"HE JUST TOOK AND
SHUT HIMSELF UP
IN THE HOUSE

22:19.212 --> 22:21.130
"AND FASTENED
ALL THE WINDOWS,

22:21.298 --> 22:23.966
"AND THEN HE WENT
TO BED, HE DID,

22:24.134 --> 22:26.344
"AND PULLED THE COVERS
UP ABOUT HIS EARS.

22:26.511 --> 22:29.180
"IF THE OTHER CREATURES
WERE GOING TO GET SCARED

22:29.348 --> 22:31.766
"AND RUN AWAY FROM
THEIR OWN HOUSE,

22:31.933 --> 22:34.268
"WHAT BUSINESS WAS
THAT OF BRER RABBIT?

22:34.436 --> 22:38.731
"BRER RABBIT, HE WENT
TO SLEEP, HE DID.

22:38.899 --> 22:40.191
THE END."

22:40.359 --> 22:41.484
[CHARLES LAUGHS]

22:41.651 --> 22:43.152
I LOVE UNCLE REMUS.

22:43.320 --> 22:46.197
READ ANOTHER
STORY, MA, PLEASE?

22:46.365 --> 22:48.115
NOT TONIGHT,
YOUNG LADY.

22:48.283 --> 22:49.992
YOU'RE GOING TO DO
WHAT BRER RABBIT DID--

22:50.160 --> 22:51.452
GO TO SLEEP.

22:51.620 --> 22:53.746
AND SLEEP, HE DID.

22:58.085 --> 23:00.127
YOU BEST GET
TO BED, TOO.

23:00.295 --> 23:02.505
NOT UNLESS YOU
TUCK ME IN AND
READ ME A STORY.

23:02.672 --> 23:04.965
I WAS SPEAKING
TO THE CHILDREN.

23:05.133 --> 23:06.092
[LAUGHTER]

23:06.259 --> 23:08.969
Charles: YOUR
MA'S RIGHT.
COME ON.

23:09.137 --> 23:10.346
- GOOD NIGHT, PA.
- GOOD NIGHT, LOVE.

23:10.514 --> 23:14.100
- GOOD NIGHT, PA.
- GOOD NIGHT, DARLING.

23:14.267 --> 23:15.393
[LAURA YAWNS]

23:15.560 --> 23:17.353
Albert: IT SURE
WAS A GOOD STORY.

23:17.521 --> 23:18.729
Laura: YEAH.

23:18.897 --> 23:22.024
THE WAY BRER RABBIT
SCARED THEM OUT OF
THEIR OWN HOUSE.

23:22.192 --> 23:23.401
YEAH.

23:23.568 --> 23:26.904
FIRST, HE SHOT
OFF HIS GUN. BANG!

23:27.072 --> 23:30.741
THEN HE SHOT OFF
HIS CANNON. BOOM!

23:30.909 --> 23:33.035
ALBERT, I ALREADY
HEARD THE STORY.

23:33.203 --> 23:38.707
NOW, COULD YOU
PLEASE BE QUIET SO I
CAN GET SOME SLEEP?

23:38.875 --> 23:42.962
MAYBE THERE IS A WAY
WE CAN HELP KEZIA
GET HER HOUSE BACK.

23:43.130 --> 23:44.296
HOW?

23:44.464 --> 23:47.049
BY SCARING
MRS. OLESON OFF
THE PROPERTY.

23:47.217 --> 23:49.885
YEAH. BUT HOW?

23:50.053 --> 23:51.262
I DON'T
KNOW YET.

23:51.430 --> 23:53.848
MAYBE KEZIA CAN
HELP US FIGURE
SOMETHING OUT.

23:54.015 --> 23:55.933
YEAH, SHE KNOWS LOTS
OF SCARY STORIES.

23:56.101 --> 23:59.061
YEAH. LET'S SEE
IF WE CAN TALK
TO HER TOMORROW.

23:59.229 --> 24:01.188
- GOOD NIGHT.
- GOOD NIGHT.

24:11.908 --> 24:12.992
DARN!

24:13.160 --> 24:14.743
WHAT?

24:14.911 --> 24:17.746
WELL, NOW I
CAN'T SLEEP.

24:17.914 --> 24:18.831
GOOD.

24:18.999 --> 24:22.293
NOW YOUR SNORING
WON'T KEEP ME AWAKE.

24:22.461 --> 24:26.297
YOU THINK,
AND I'LL SLEEP.

24:41.146 --> 24:43.689
[HARRIET LAUGHING
AND CHATTERING]

24:59.122 --> 25:01.916
[APPLAUSE]

25:02.083 --> 25:03.876
THERE SHE...

25:04.044 --> 25:05.669
BLOWS.

25:05.837 --> 25:10.049
SHE SWIMS
LIKE A PREGNANT
PENGUIN, SHE DOES.

25:12.511 --> 25:15.888
PSST.
KEZIA.

25:16.056 --> 25:17.640
KEZIA!

25:27.025 --> 25:30.569
YOU'RE A SIGHT FOR
SORE EYES, DEARIES.

25:30.737 --> 25:33.280
WHEREVER HAVE
YOU BEEN KEEPING
YOURSELVES?

25:33.448 --> 25:34.990
THE OLESONS DON'T
WANT US HERE.

25:35.158 --> 25:37.326
AND WE DON'T
WANT THEM HERE
ON YOUR LAND,

25:37.494 --> 25:39.495
MAKING YOU WORK
YOUR FINGERS
TO THE BONE.

25:39.663 --> 25:44.625
OH, THERE'S NOTHING MUCH
WE CAN DO ABOUT IT, LOVES.

25:44.793 --> 25:46.001
MAYBE THERE IS, KEZIA.

25:46.169 --> 25:48.963
MAYBE WE CAN SCARE
THEM OFF THE PROPERTY.

25:49.130 --> 25:50.589
Andy: BUT WE
DON'T KNOW HOW.

25:50.757 --> 25:53.384
Albert: YEAH, WE
WERE FIGURING MAYBE
YOU'D HAVE AN IDEA.

25:53.552 --> 25:55.427
YEAH, YOU'VE
BEEN EVERYWHERE,

25:55.595 --> 25:56.887
SEEN EVERYTHING
THERE IS.

25:57.055 --> 25:58.514
COULD YOU THINK
OF SOMETHING

25:58.682 --> 26:00.849
THAT WOULD
SCARE THE PANTS
OFF OF THEM?

26:01.017 --> 26:04.770
OH, I WISH I KNEW.

26:04.938 --> 26:06.564
Albert: HEY,
WAIT A MINUTE.

26:06.731 --> 26:10.276
REMEMBER WHAT
YOU TOLD US ABOUT
THE MONSTER?

26:10.443 --> 26:12.319
UH, WHAT WAS
HIS NAME?

26:12.487 --> 26:14.113
LOCH NESS.

26:14.281 --> 26:15.864
YEAH.

26:16.032 --> 26:18.993
THE LOCH NESS.

26:19.160 --> 26:22.538
WHAT IF THERE
WAS A MONSTER
IN THIS LAKE?

26:26.418 --> 26:29.378
WHAT IF
THERE WAS?

26:29.546 --> 26:32.089
[LAUGHTER]

26:38.221 --> 26:40.389
[SNORING]

26:49.774 --> 26:51.817
[LOUD BELLOW]

26:51.985 --> 26:53.819
OH.

26:53.987 --> 26:55.779
OH, NELS.

26:55.947 --> 26:58.282
STOP THAT SNORING.

26:58.450 --> 27:01.619
[LOUD BELLOW]

27:01.786 --> 27:03.579
NELS, STOP!

27:04.914 --> 27:07.291
OH. OH, NELS
IS NOT HERE.

27:07.459 --> 27:09.168
[LOUD BELLOW]

27:09.336 --> 27:11.837
MOTHER,
WHAT IS THAT
HORRIBLE NOISE?

27:12.005 --> 27:13.756
OH...

27:13.923 --> 27:15.841
OH, I
DON'T KNOW.

27:16.009 --> 27:17.259
[GROANS]

27:17.427 --> 27:18.761
BUT I'M
GOING TO...

27:18.928 --> 27:20.721
I'M GOING
TO FIND OUT.

27:20.889 --> 27:23.015
DON'T JUST
STAND THERE,
COME ON.

27:23.183 --> 27:26.310
[LOUD BELLOWING]

27:26.478 --> 27:28.354
IT'S HIM!

27:28.521 --> 27:29.521
WHO "HIM"?

27:29.689 --> 27:33.484
I CALL HIM
THE LAKE KEZIA
MONSTER.

27:33.652 --> 27:34.943
UH, IT'S
LAKE HARRIET.

27:35.111 --> 27:36.487
WHAT MONSTER?

27:36.655 --> 27:43.285
OH, SOMETHING LIKE
THEM MONSTERS THEY HAVE
IN THE SCOTTISH LAKES.

27:43.453 --> 27:45.120
THEY CALL THEM LOCHS.

27:45.288 --> 27:46.455
AH!

27:46.623 --> 27:49.667
NONSENSE! THERE'S
NO SUCH THING
AS A MONSTER.

27:49.834 --> 27:52.211
I READ ABOUT
THOSE MONSTERS
IN SCHOOL.

27:52.379 --> 27:55.714
THERE'S ONE IN LOCH NESS.
A LOT OF PEOPLE SAW HIM.

27:55.882 --> 27:57.132
- OH.
- YEAH.

27:57.300 --> 27:59.468
LIKE THE TERRIBLE,
FEARSOME THING

27:59.636 --> 28:03.055
THAT LURKS IN THESE
WATERS OUT THERE.

28:03.223 --> 28:04.682
DID YOU EVER
SEE HIM?

28:04.849 --> 28:06.850
Kezia: SHIVER ME
TIMBERS, CHILD.

28:07.018 --> 28:10.646
I SEEN HIM EVERY MONTH
SINCE I BEEN HERE.

28:10.814 --> 28:12.231
YES, LIKE CLOCKWORK,

28:12.399 --> 28:15.984
HE STARTS THAT
INFERNAL BELLOWING,

28:16.152 --> 28:20.864
GETTING READY TO
RISE ON THE NIGHT
OF THE FULL MOON.

28:21.032 --> 28:21.990
YES...

28:22.158 --> 28:25.661
SEEKING HUMAN FODDER,
SO THE STORY GOES,

28:25.829 --> 28:28.163
IN REVENGE FOR A MATE

28:28.331 --> 28:32.501
WHO WAS KILLED
OVER 100 YEARS AGO.

28:32.669 --> 28:34.086
[LAUGHS]

28:34.254 --> 28:38.632
DO YOU EXPECT ME
TO BELIEVE SUCH
AN OUTLANDISH TALE?

28:38.800 --> 28:40.134
Kezia: YOU
CAN BELIEVE
IT OR NOT.

28:40.301 --> 28:42.177
IT'S YOUR
MONSTER NOW.

28:42.345 --> 28:44.763
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
IT'S MY MONSTER NOW?

28:44.931 --> 28:47.766
WELL, IT GOES
WITH THE PROPERTY...

28:47.934 --> 28:49.601
AND ITS CURSE.

28:49.769 --> 28:52.730
IT'S PROBABLY
WHY THE CLARKS
PULLED UP STAKES

28:52.897 --> 28:54.565
AND WENT TO
CALIFORNIA.

28:54.733 --> 28:58.277
Kezia: ABANDONED
THE PLACE BEFORE
THEY WAS DEVOURED.

28:58.445 --> 28:59.528
[LOUD BELLOWING]

28:59.696 --> 29:02.531
OH! POPPYCOCK! HA HA!

29:02.699 --> 29:04.324
WHY DIDN'T HE
COME AFTER YOU?

29:04.492 --> 29:05.743
HE DID...

29:05.910 --> 29:07.828
SLATHERING
AND SLURPING...

29:07.996 --> 29:09.705
EVERY MONTH!

29:09.873 --> 29:10.956
WHY'D YOU STAY?

29:11.124 --> 29:12.082
Harriet: YEAH.

29:12.250 --> 29:14.376
Kezia: WELL, I HAD
NO PLACE ELSE TO GO,

29:14.544 --> 29:15.627
NOT LIKE YOU,

29:15.795 --> 29:18.881
WITH A FINE
PLACE OF YOUR OWN
IN WALNUT GROVE.

29:19.048 --> 29:23.135
BESIDES, HE DIDN'T
LIKE THIS HARPOON,
HE DIDN'T.

29:23.303 --> 29:27.222
WELL, YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT I THINK, KEZIA?

29:27.390 --> 29:30.058
I THINK YOU ARE
A MONUMENTAL LIAR,

29:30.226 --> 29:32.144
AND YOU'RE JUST SAYING
ALL THIS NONSENSE

29:32.312 --> 29:35.814
TO TRY AND SCARE
ME OFF MY PROPERTY
AND MY LAKE.

29:35.982 --> 29:37.649
SO DO I.

29:37.817 --> 29:39.276
ME TOO.

29:39.444 --> 29:42.029
Harriet: NOW,
I THINK THAT IT
IS NOTHING MORE

29:42.197 --> 29:43.989
THAN A SICK COW
MAKING THAT NOISE,

29:44.157 --> 29:47.159
AND IF I HEAR
ANY MORE NONSENSE
ABOUT MONSTERS,

29:47.327 --> 29:48.619
YOU WILL BE FIRED.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.621
CHILDREN, TO BED.

29:52.290 --> 29:55.083
[LOUD BELLOWING]

30:03.384 --> 30:04.843
[BELLOW]

30:05.011 --> 30:06.345
[LAUGHING]

30:06.513 --> 30:07.846
[BELLOW]

30:08.014 --> 30:09.681
[LAUGHING]

30:09.849 --> 30:11.767
[BELLOW]

30:15.438 --> 30:18.524
YOU CAN STOP
NOW, LOVES.

30:18.691 --> 30:21.860
HER LADYSHIP
WOULDN'T BUY IT.

30:22.028 --> 30:23.737
DARN.

30:23.905 --> 30:27.407
BUT THANKS
FOR TRYING
ALL THE SAME.

30:27.575 --> 30:31.703
WELL, I BEST
GET TO BED NOW.

30:31.871 --> 30:35.749
I GOT A BIG
DAY TOMORROW.

30:35.917 --> 30:37.960
GOOD NIGHT, ALL.

30:38.127 --> 30:40.546
Children:
GOOD NIGHT, KEZIA.

30:43.466 --> 30:47.386
AW, GEE. WHAT
ARE WE GOING
TO DO NOW?

30:47.554 --> 30:51.807
WELL, YOU KNOW
WHAT THEY SAY--
SEEING IS BELIEVING.

30:51.975 --> 30:53.308
SO?

30:53.476 --> 30:56.854
SO WE'LL MAKE A
MONSTER SHE CAN SEE.

30:57.021 --> 30:58.564
WHAT KIND OF MONSTER?

30:58.731 --> 31:03.151
OH, ONE THAT WILL REALLY
SCARE HARRIET OLESON
OUT OF HER PANTS.

31:03.319 --> 31:05.445
THAT I'D LOVE TO SEE.

31:05.613 --> 31:10.367
WELL, WE BEST BE
GETTING HOME NOW.
I'LL TELL YOU ON THE WAY.

31:10.535 --> 31:13.662
ARE YOU SURE THERE'S NO
SUCH THING AS MONSTERS?

31:13.830 --> 31:16.832
GO TO SLEEP,
WILLIE.

31:17.000 --> 31:19.251
[SNORING]

31:19.419 --> 31:20.544
WHAT'S THAT?

31:20.712 --> 31:22.170
IT'S ONLY MOTHER.

31:22.338 --> 31:24.172
[LOUD SNORING]

31:24.340 --> 31:26.174
OH, YEAH.

31:49.866 --> 31:51.366
GOOD MORNING,
MR. OLESON.

31:51.534 --> 31:53.243
WELL, GOOD MORNING,
LAURA. WHAT CAN I
DO FOR YOU?

31:53.411 --> 31:55.787
HOW MUCH GLUE
AND TACKS COULD I
BUY FOR 15 CENTS?

31:55.955 --> 31:57.706
GLUE AND TACKS?
WHAT ARE YOU
WORKING ON?

31:57.874 --> 32:01.209
WELL, IT'S
A SPECIAL PROJECT,
SORT OF AN INVENTION.

32:01.377 --> 32:03.128
WELL, I'LL TELL
YOU WHAT--I LIKE
TO ENCOURAGE

32:03.296 --> 32:04.880
CHILDREN'S
EDUCATIONAL
PROJECTS.

32:05.048 --> 32:06.465
I'LL JUST DONATE
WHATEVER YOU NEED.

32:06.633 --> 32:09.426
THANKS, MR. OLESON!
I'LL NEED ABOUT
A GALLON OF GLUE

32:09.594 --> 32:11.219
AND ABOUT A COUPLE
POUNDS OF TACKS.

32:11.387 --> 32:12.346
[WHISTLES]

32:12.513 --> 32:13.931
MMM, MUST BE QUITE
A BIG PROJECT.

32:14.098 --> 32:16.391
OH, THE BIGGER,
THE BETTER,
I ALWAYS SAY.

32:16.559 --> 32:17.893
WELL,
ANYTHING ELSE?

32:18.061 --> 32:20.354
WELL, COULD
YOU SPARE

32:20.521 --> 32:22.522
ABOUT 10 YARDS OF
BURLAP SACKING?

32:22.690 --> 32:24.816
10 YARDS
OF BURLAP...
WELL, LET'S SEE.

32:24.984 --> 32:29.071
WE GOT, UH...WELL,
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE
WHAT'S LEFT HERE?

32:29.238 --> 32:30.614
IT'S AT LEAST
10 YARDS.

32:30.782 --> 32:32.324
IS THAT ALL?

32:32.492 --> 32:34.493
LET ME THINK.

32:34.661 --> 32:39.122
I KNOW IT'S AN AWFUL
LOT, BUT A COUPLE
OF ROMAN CANDLES?

32:39.290 --> 32:40.499
ROMAN CANDLES?

32:40.667 --> 32:42.668
WELL, THAT SOUNDS
VERY INTERESTING.

32:42.835 --> 32:44.586
UH, HOW ABOUT
3 OF THEM?

32:44.754 --> 32:46.880
NEVER KNOW
WHEN YOU MIGHT
NEED A SPARE.

32:47.048 --> 32:50.509
GEE, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO THANK YOU,
MR. OLESON.

32:50.677 --> 32:52.594
OH...THINK
NOTHING OF IT.

32:52.762 --> 32:53.845
GLAD TO HELP.

32:54.013 --> 32:55.597
I JUST HOPE THE
PROJECT WORKS.

32:55.765 --> 32:57.683
IF IT DOES, YOU'LL
HEAR ABOUT IT.

32:57.850 --> 32:59.142
- GOOD.
- THANKS AGAIN!

32:59.310 --> 33:01.478
ALL RIGHT. GOOD LUCK!

33:02.522 --> 33:03.939
- HI, PA. HI, PA.
- OH, HI, BOY.

33:04.107 --> 33:05.190
HEY, WHAT YOU
UP TO, FELLOWS?

33:05.358 --> 33:06.984
WE'VE COME
TO GET SOME
SCRAP WOOD.

33:07.151 --> 33:09.820
THERE'S A WHOLE STACK
OF IT OVER THERE.
TAKE WHAT YOU NEED.

33:09.988 --> 33:11.446
- THANKS.
- THANKS.

33:11.614 --> 33:12.698
BUILDING SOMETHING?

33:12.865 --> 33:14.658
- YES, SIR.
- LIKE WHAT?

33:14.826 --> 33:17.244
WE HAVEN'T
DECIDED YET.

33:17.412 --> 33:19.413
[JONATHAN LAUGHS]

33:19.580 --> 33:21.581
Albert: YOU
SURE WERE LUCKY
AT OLESON'S.

33:21.749 --> 33:23.875
WE CAN MAKE THE
MONSTER AS BIG
AS WE WANT NOW.

33:24.043 --> 33:25.585
Andy: HOW LONG
DO YOU THINK
IT'LL TAKE?

33:25.753 --> 33:28.630
WELL, WE
HAVE TO GET IT
DONE IN 3 DAYS.

33:28.798 --> 33:30.298
THAT'S WHEN
THE MOON WILL
BE FULL.

33:30.466 --> 33:33.635
IN THE MEANTIME, WE'LL
JUST KEEP SCARING
THEM A LITTLE BIT,

33:33.803 --> 33:35.971
KEEP THEM
THINKING ABOUT
THE MONSTER.

33:36.139 --> 33:39.599
Laura: OH, I
CAN'T WAIT UNTIL
THAT FULL MOON.

33:39.767 --> 33:41.977
WE'LL WORK
ON IT AT OUR
CLUBHOUSE.

33:42.145 --> 33:43.979
WE DON'T
WANT OUR FOLKS
FINDING OUT.

33:44.147 --> 33:45.147
RIGHT.

33:45.314 --> 33:46.356
WELL, PA
WOULDN'T MIND.

33:46.524 --> 33:48.066
WE CAN'T TAKE
THAT RISK.

33:48.234 --> 33:51.445
ALBERT'S
RIGHT,
LAURA.

33:51.612 --> 33:55.323
THE ONLY THING
WORRYING ME IS
BUILDING THAT HEAD.

33:55.491 --> 33:57.325
IT'S GOT TO
LOOK REAL SCARY.

33:57.493 --> 33:59.161
YEAH.

33:59.328 --> 34:01.496
HEY! I GOT
AN IDEA.

34:01.664 --> 34:02.664
YOU GUYS
GO AHEAD.

34:02.832 --> 34:05.000
I'LL MEET
YOU AT THE
CLUBHOUSE.

34:09.422 --> 34:11.006
COME ON.

34:16.179 --> 34:17.179
HI, MA!

34:17.346 --> 34:19.306
YOU'RE HOME
EARLY TODAY.

34:19.474 --> 34:20.599
IS PA HOME?

34:20.767 --> 34:24.311
NO, HE'S MAKING
A DELIVERY
TO SLEEPY EYE.

34:24.479 --> 34:27.522
THAT OLD MOOSE
HEAD SURE LOOKS
UGLY UP THERE.

34:27.690 --> 34:28.857
SURE DOES.

34:29.025 --> 34:31.068
PA SHOULDN'T
HAVE PUT IT
IN THE HOUSE.

34:31.235 --> 34:33.528
I TOLD HIM THAT.

34:33.696 --> 34:35.197
WHY DON'T WE
TAKE IT DOWN?

34:35.364 --> 34:37.032
HE PROBABLY
WON'T EVEN
MISS IT.

34:37.200 --> 34:39.743
MMM, I'D LOVE TO.

34:39.911 --> 34:41.870
WELL, WHY
DON'T WE?

34:42.038 --> 34:45.332
WE CAN ALWAYS
PUT IT BACK
UP LATER.

34:45.500 --> 34:48.752
AFTER ALL,
MA, IT'S YOUR
HOUSE, TOO.

34:50.546 --> 34:52.923
YOU'RE
ABSOLUTELY
RIGHT.

34:53.091 --> 34:55.467
ANDREW,
TAKE IT DOWN.

34:55.635 --> 34:56.676
[LAUGHS]

34:56.844 --> 34:59.888
[WILLIE LAUGHING]

35:00.056 --> 35:02.265
Willie:
YOU'RE ALL WET!

35:03.726 --> 35:04.726
[HARRIET LAUGHS]

35:04.894 --> 35:06.895
Nellie: GET IN
ALL THE WAY!

35:07.063 --> 35:08.730
OH, NO, DARLING,
NOT TODAY.

35:08.898 --> 35:10.524
I DON'T
WANT TO GET
MY HAIR WET.

35:10.691 --> 35:15.028
OH, IN THAT BATHING
SUIT, SHE LOOKS LIKE
A HOT AIR BALLOON.

35:18.074 --> 35:19.908
WHAT DID YOU SAY, KEZIA?

35:20.076 --> 35:21.743
OH. OH,
NOTHING, MA'AM,

35:21.911 --> 35:26.373
JUST THAT I'LL
HAVE SNAPPED ALL
THESE BEANS BY NOON.

35:26.541 --> 35:29.251
UH...WELL, YOU'D BETTER.

35:43.766 --> 35:45.517
ALL RIGHT...

35:45.685 --> 35:48.311
NOW, I'LL
GET WILLIE.

35:48.479 --> 35:52.274
AND, ANDY,
YOU GET
NELLIE.

35:52.441 --> 35:55.694
MRS. OLESON'S
ALL YOURS,
LAURA.

35:58.114 --> 35:59.698
LET'S GO.

36:55.755 --> 36:57.464
AAH! OH! OH!
OH, MY, OH!

36:57.632 --> 36:58.924
OW! OW!

36:59.091 --> 37:00.759
OW! WHAT
WAS THAT?

37:00.927 --> 37:02.844
OW! AAH!

37:03.012 --> 37:05.931
AAH! OH, MY! OH,
WHAT WAS THAT?

37:06.098 --> 37:08.934
AAH! OH,
MY TOE!

37:09.101 --> 37:10.352
Willie: OUCH!

37:10.519 --> 37:12.479
COME ON,
DARLINGS.
COME ON.

37:12.647 --> 37:13.813
OH, CAREFUL.

37:13.981 --> 37:15.023
MY LEG!

37:15.191 --> 37:17.317
OH! NELLIE, WHAT
DID I TELL YOU?

37:17.485 --> 37:18.902
THERE'S A MONSTER
OUT THERE!

37:19.070 --> 37:22.030
OH, DARLING,
I'M SURE IT'S JUST
NOTHING BUT A CRAB.

37:22.198 --> 37:26.034
SOME LITTLE CRAB!
IT ALMOST BIT
MY LEG OFF!

37:26.202 --> 37:29.162
YOU KNOW WHAT
IT IS TOMORROW.

37:29.330 --> 37:30.664
DO I KNOW WHAT
TOMORROW IS?

37:30.831 --> 37:33.500
OF COURSE I KNOW
WHAT TOMORROW IS.
IT'S THURSDAY.

37:33.668 --> 37:37.212
YEAH, AND THE NEXT DAY?

37:37.380 --> 37:40.340
WELL, OBVIOUSLY
IT'S FRIDAY.

37:40.508 --> 37:44.052
THE MOON WILL BE FULL.

37:46.264 --> 37:48.640
OH, GET BACK
TO WORK.

37:52.103 --> 37:57.148
NOW, WILLIE, DARLING,
I'M SURE THAT THERE
IS NO MONSTER.

37:57.316 --> 37:59.192
NOW, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I WANT YOU TO DO.

37:59.360 --> 38:02.988
I WANT YOU TO GO
INTO TOWN TOMORROW

38:03.155 --> 38:05.782
AND TELL YOUR FATHER
TO GIVE YOU THE SHOTGUN.

38:05.950 --> 38:07.075
BUT IF THERE'S
NO MONSTER--

38:07.243 --> 38:09.286
OH, DON'T
ARGUE WITH ME!

38:09.453 --> 38:11.788
JUST DO IT!

38:11.956 --> 38:13.206
[POLLY CAWS]

38:13.374 --> 38:15.875
Polly: MONSTER'S COMING.
THE MONSTER'S COMING.

38:16.043 --> 38:21.548
OH, FOR HEAVEN'S
SAKE, THAT AWFUL BIRD!

38:21.716 --> 38:24.259
I'M GOING TO SHOOT
IT WITH A SHOTGUN.

38:29.974 --> 38:32.058
LAND SAKES! I THOUGHT
YOU'D NEVER GET HOME.

38:32.226 --> 38:34.602
I'LL, UH, HEAT
UP SOME SUPPER.

38:34.770 --> 38:36.313
NEVER MIND,
I'M TOO
TIRED TO EAT.

38:36.480 --> 38:40.108
I'M JUST GOING TO GO
ON AND GET SOME SLEEP.
WHERE'S ANDY?

38:40.276 --> 38:42.861
HE WENT FROGGING AGAIN
WITH LAURA AND ALBERT.

38:43.029 --> 38:45.864
YEAH, WELL, I'M
GOING TO GET
ME SOME REST.

38:50.619 --> 38:52.787
WHERE'S MY
MOOSE HEAD?

38:54.999 --> 38:56.833
[BELLOWING]

39:35.831 --> 39:38.708
[CAWING]

39:40.044 --> 39:42.796
FULL MOON
TONIGHT.

39:42.963 --> 39:44.506
[CAWING]

39:44.673 --> 39:48.218
Harriet: OH! I'M TIRED
OF LISTENING TO THAT!

39:48.386 --> 39:49.677
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING?

39:49.845 --> 39:52.347
HONING ME HARPOON, MA'AM.

39:52.515 --> 39:53.848
WHY?

39:54.016 --> 39:56.101
I DOES IT EVERY MONTH.

39:56.268 --> 39:59.145
FORCE OF HABIT,
AS YOU MIGHT SAY.

39:59.313 --> 40:01.272
Polly: FULL
MOON TONIGHT.

40:01.440 --> 40:04.401
FULL MOON TONIGHT.
FULL MOON TONIGHT.

40:04.568 --> 40:07.904
OH! YOU TRAINED THAT
BIRD TO SAY THAT.

40:08.072 --> 40:10.115
- ME, MA'AM?
- YES.

40:10.282 --> 40:11.408
NO, MA'AM.

40:11.575 --> 40:13.785
POLLY HAS A
MIND OF HIS OWN.

40:13.953 --> 40:15.703
YOU'VE HEARD
THE OLD SAYING--

40:15.871 --> 40:19.332
YOU CAN'T TEACH AN OLD
PARROT NEW TRICKS.

40:19.500 --> 40:21.292
THAT IS NOT A PARROT!

40:21.460 --> 40:22.377
[SIGHS]

40:22.545 --> 40:24.546
WHAT ARE WE HAVING
FOR SUPPER TONIGHT?

40:24.713 --> 40:27.173
FISH...

40:27.341 --> 40:31.177
A VERY LARGE FISH...

40:31.345 --> 40:34.264
AN ENORMOUS FISH.

40:34.432 --> 40:38.351
OH. WELL, START
PREPARING IT.

40:38.519 --> 40:39.644
ANY GUESTS?

40:39.812 --> 40:41.771
Harriet:
NO, NO GUESTS.

40:41.939 --> 40:44.149
NO ONE WILL COME
OUT HERE ANYMORE.

40:44.316 --> 40:47.652
SOMEONE HAS
BEEN TELLING THEM
ABOUT OUR MONSTER.

40:47.820 --> 40:49.946
THERE ARE NO
MONSTERS HERE!

40:50.114 --> 40:52.532
OH, FOR
HEAVEN'S SAKES!

40:52.700 --> 40:55.952
FULL MOON
TONIGHT.

40:56.120 --> 40:58.121
[CAWS]

40:58.289 --> 40:59.747
ABSOLUTELY NOT!

40:59.915 --> 41:01.833
I AM NOT GOING TO
GIVE YOU THAT SHOTGUN.

41:02.001 --> 41:04.961
BUT IF YOU DON'T GIVE IT
TO ME, MA WILL JUST COME
HERE AND GET IT HERSELF.

41:05.129 --> 41:06.379
ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GET IT.

41:06.547 --> 41:08.089
ABSOLUTELY
RIDICULOUS, THIS
MONSTER BUSINESS.

41:08.257 --> 41:11.134
IT SERVES HER RIGHT
FOR TAKING THAT
OLD LADY'S LAND!

41:11.302 --> 41:14.095
[DOORBELL JINGLES]

41:14.263 --> 41:16.055
WHAT YOU DOING
HERE, WILLIE?

41:16.223 --> 41:17.891
I THOUGHT YOU'D
BE SWIMMING TODAY.

41:18.058 --> 41:20.643
NOT ME. I'M NOT
GOING IN THAT LAKE.

41:20.811 --> 41:22.103
THE MONSTER BIT ME!

41:22.271 --> 41:23.605
YOU'RE KIDDING.

41:23.772 --> 41:25.190
HERE'S THE
SHOTGUN.

41:25.357 --> 41:26.941
THANKS.

41:29.987 --> 41:32.238
WHAT DOES HE NEED
A SHOTGUN FOR?

41:32.406 --> 41:36.576
HIS MOTHER THINKS
SHE'S GOING TO
SHOOT A MONSTER.

41:36.744 --> 41:40.246
BUT ISN'T THAT
KIND OF DANGEROUS?

41:40.414 --> 41:42.123
NOT REALLY.

41:42.291 --> 41:44.125
JUST BETWEEN YOU AND ME,

41:44.293 --> 41:46.961
I LOADED IT WITH BLANKS.

42:47.314 --> 42:50.316
FULLEST MOON
I EVER SEEN.

42:50.484 --> 42:51.484
[SIGHS]

42:51.652 --> 42:54.195
BE QUIET.
I'M EATING!

42:54.363 --> 42:57.282
I IMAGINE HE
WILL, TOO...

42:57.449 --> 42:59.033
TONIGHT.

43:13.882 --> 43:15.258
Laura: IS
EVERYBODY READY?

43:15.426 --> 43:16.551
Albert: ALL SET.

43:16.719 --> 43:18.011
Andy: FINE
BACK HERE.

43:18.178 --> 43:19.304
YOU TOLD KEZIA
NOT TO WORRY

43:19.471 --> 43:21.014
ABOUT THE SHOTGUN,
DIDN'T YOU?

43:21.181 --> 43:24.058
Laura: YEAH.
LET'S GO.

43:35.112 --> 43:36.154
[LOUD BELLOW]

43:36.322 --> 43:37.989
- OH! MY GOODNESS!
- HE'S COMING, HE IS!

43:38.157 --> 43:40.742
- MOTHER!
- THE SHOTGUN!

43:40.909 --> 43:42.160
GET THE GUN,
WILLIE!

43:42.328 --> 43:43.286
MOTHER!

43:43.454 --> 43:44.787
SHUT UP!
SHUT UP!
BE QUIET!

43:44.955 --> 43:46.623
[LOUD BELLOW]

43:46.790 --> 43:49.751
WE'LL JUST SEE
HOW BRAVE THIS
MONSTER IS.

43:49.918 --> 43:51.377
AREN'T YOU
COMING?

43:51.545 --> 43:52.754
OH, NO, MA'AM.

43:52.921 --> 43:55.590
I'LL JUST STAY HERE
AND PRAY FOR YOU.

43:55.758 --> 43:56.924
OH, FOR HEAVEN'S SAKES.

43:57.092 --> 43:59.927
- MOTHER!
- SHH! QUIET. SHH!

44:02.306 --> 44:06.517
[LOUD BELLOW]

44:06.685 --> 44:08.853
[WHISPERING]
GET OFF MY SKIRT.

44:09.021 --> 44:12.148
[LOUD BELLOWING]

44:35.923 --> 44:38.091
[BELLOWING]

44:49.770 --> 44:51.229
AAH! AAH!

44:51.397 --> 44:53.189
OH! OH!

44:53.357 --> 44:55.483
OH! IT--IT--

44:55.651 --> 45:00.655
Harriet:
IT IS--IT IS--
IT IS--IT IS--

45:00.823 --> 45:03.574
IT IS A MONSTER!
OH!

45:03.742 --> 45:04.784
SHOOT IT!

45:04.952 --> 45:07.203
YES!
SHOOT IT!

45:07.371 --> 45:10.164
KILL IT!
KILL IT!

45:10.332 --> 45:12.250
YOU'VE GOT
THE GUN!

45:12.418 --> 45:13.710
OH!

45:13.877 --> 45:16.212
OH! YES! YES!

45:16.380 --> 45:18.548
[HARRIET SCREAMS]

45:22.886 --> 45:25.012
[BELLOWING]

45:44.074 --> 45:47.201
OH, LORD!
OH, LORD!

45:47.369 --> 45:51.330
IT'S NO USE!
IT WON'T STOP!

45:51.498 --> 45:54.333
OH! RUN, CHILDREN!

45:54.501 --> 45:56.878
RUN FOR YOUR LIVES!

45:57.045 --> 45:59.130
OH, MY GOD!

46:09.475 --> 46:10.600
Laura:
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

46:10.768 --> 46:13.311
THEY'RE HALFWAY
TO WALNUT GROVE
BY NOW.

46:13.479 --> 46:14.395
[LAUGHS]

46:14.563 --> 46:17.148
Albert: COME ON.
LET'S GO SEE KEZIA.

46:17.316 --> 46:19.275
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

46:28.619 --> 46:30.036
WE DID IT!
WE DID IT!

46:30.204 --> 46:31.454
[BOTH LAUGHING]

46:31.622 --> 46:33.414
Kezia: OH,
I KNOW!
I KNOW!

46:33.582 --> 46:35.416
Albert:
THEY'LL NEVER
COME BACK! NEVER!

46:35.584 --> 46:38.628
Andy:
AND YOUR TAXES
ARE ALL PAID UP!

46:38.796 --> 46:41.464
OH, HALLELUJAH!

46:41.632 --> 46:43.466
All: HALLELUJAH!

46:43.634 --> 46:46.010
[LOUD GROANING]

47:03.070 --> 47:04.779
[LAUGHTER]

47:10.869 --> 47:14.288
I CAME OUT TO SEE WHAT
ALL THE FUSS WAS ABOUT,

47:14.456 --> 47:19.001
AND I GOT TO
LAUGHING SO HARD,
I FELL IN THE LAKE!

47:19.169 --> 47:21.295
[ALL LAUGHING]

47:23.799 --> 47:26.634
YOU WON'T TELL
ON US, WILL YOU?

47:26.802 --> 47:27.885
NEVER!

47:28.053 --> 47:29.387
HO HO HO!

47:29.555 --> 47:31.973
NEVER!

47:32.140 --> 47:34.141
NOW, UH...

47:34.309 --> 47:37.311
WHY DON'T YOU
CLEAN YOURSELF UP

47:37.479 --> 47:39.272
AND STAY AND
HAVE SOME SUPPER?

47:39.439 --> 47:42.817
WE'RE HAVING
A LARGE FISH...

47:42.985 --> 47:45.319
AN ENORMOUS FISH.

47:45.487 --> 47:47.321
[ALL LAUGHING]

47:49.950 --> 47:52.326
I DON'T MIND IF I DO!

47:52.494 --> 47:54.912
[ALL LAUGHING]
